    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-02-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-02-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="212"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d212">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/2379</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_PTN1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-02-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 3, 1916</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received 7.30 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3703. Passengers and crew <hi rend="italic">Kashgar</hi> already dispersed before
                    receipt of your 2786,<note n="1" xml:id="d212fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_152">p. 152</ref>.</note>
                    January 26. Nothing known of reports concerning her or the <hi rend="italic"
                        >City of Marseilles</hi>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
